item.title: This is so annoying can anyone figure it out
item.dc:creator: @kneistol kneistol
item.description:
@kneistol wrote:

hey when u go to compile click edit and delete all off it and add this

@echo off
if exist “%programfiles%\Java” (call :compile “%programfiles%\Java”) else (goto error)
:compile
for /D %%x in ("%~1jdk*") do (set p="%%~x\bin\javac.exe")
if defined p (%p% -cp . *.java)
if defined p (goto end)
:error
echo You do not have Java installed. Please download it at the site that is about to load.
“%programfiles%\Internet Explorer\iexplore.exe” http://java.sun.com/javase/downloads/index.jsp
:end
echo Finished!
pause
exit

hope it helps

@King_Lingerz wrote:

[quote=“trytohaxme, post:4, topic:300708”]You need the class clickingMost -.-

Here I’ll upload mine for you…

http://uppit.com/v/668BJD8C

Download that and put it into your server files.[/quote]

Isn’t he declaring them wrong? Java is case sensitive, so it should be:

clickingMost = new ClickingMost;
public static clickingMost ClickingMost = null;

Not sure if I’m right but I reckon that’s probably why.
